"v.喜欢，高兴 【英】 v. 喜欢，高兴(to feel joy or great delight) 【考】 反义词：grouse(抱怨 ) 【记】 re(反复)+joice(=joy 高兴) 【例】 to rejoice at good news v. 使高兴 【记】re反复, jo = joy, ice: 在夏天反复用ice使你joy－使高兴rejoice是""quot;飘柔""quot;的商标 【反】grouse(v 埋怨; 抱怨) 【记】re + joy rejoice (v.)  c.1300, ""to own, possess, enjoy the possession of, have the fruition of,"" from Old French rejoiss-, present participle stem of rejoir, resjoir ""gladden, rejoice,"" from re-, which here is of obscure signification, perhaps an intensive (see re-), + joir ""be glad,"" from Latin gaudere ""rejoice"" (see joy). Originally sense in to rejoice in. Meaning ""to be full of joy"" is recorded from late 14c. Middle English also used simple verb joy ""to feel gladness; to rejoice"" (mid-13c.) and rejoy (early 14c.). Related: Rejoiced; rejoicing."
